 {"id": "frankenredis-st3p", "title": "Add semantic fuzz target for fr-store PFADD/PFCOUNT/PFMERGE invariants", "description": "Evidence: HyperLogLog operations are implemented in crates/fr-store/src/lib.rs:7687 (pfadd), 7736 (pfcount), and 7758 (pfmerge), with only unit tests today. No dedicated fuzz harness checks hostile register payloads, merge idempotence, or monotonic count expectations.\\n\\nNeed: add a structure-aware fuzz target that drives multiple HLL keys through PFADD/PFCOUNT/PFMERGE sequences and asserts semantic invariants: repeated adds do not shrink counts, merges are idempotent, merging identical sources is stable, type errors do not mutate existing HLLs, and dump/restore preserves approximate counts within deterministic self-roundtrip bounds.\\n\\nReal impl path: fuzz/Cargo.toml plus new fuzz/fuzz_targets/fuzz_store_hll.rs hitting the fr-store PF* APIs directly.", "status": "closed", "priority": 3, "issue_type": "task", "created_at": "2026-04-22T17:48:34Z", "created_by": "cod-redis", "updated_at": "2026-04-22T21:22:20.222778031Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-22T21:22:20.222778031Z", "close_reason": "Completed", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "labels": ["fr-store", "fuzz", "testing"]}
